``` EXAMPLE Splunk SPL — agent token/request spike (see .yml).
    Dynamic baseline version: compare each agent's 5-min volume to its own recent average
    instead of a fixed number, so busy agents don't alert constantly. ```

index=agent_audit event=model_request
| bin _time span=5m
| stats sum(tokens) as tokens count as requests by _time agent_id
| eventstats avg(requests) as avg_req stdev(requests) as sd_req by agent_id
| eval threshold = avg_req + (3 * sd_req)
| where requests > threshold AND requests > 50
| table _time agent_id requests avg_req tokens
| sort - requests
